  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nThe primary nav to select communities disappears or becomes unresponsive when using a mouse scroll wheel. This makes is impossible or difficult to reach communities that are not currently displayed. \r\n\r\nAlthough the list can be clicked on and dragged as well, it's not particularly intuitive and we use scrollbars elsewhere. The navigation becomes visible again after touching the touchpad, but not everyone will have one.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/50769329/a45bab1a-7492-4ca8-9003-ef943369bd46\r\n\r\nA similar behaviour is seen when scrolling in other parts of the app.\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/50769329/6f333ac9-d6ac-4abb-afe5-02261c1c5c13)\r\n\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nUse a scroll wheel over a scrollable component in both directions and at various speeds\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nSmooth scrolling\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nUnresponsive scrolling, or components disappearing from view\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status desktop version: 0.14 RC3 (has also been seen in previous versions)\r\n- Operating System: Mac\r\n- Mouse: Logitech MX Master 3\r\n\r\n",
